<div class="sh" style="margin-top:20px"><h2>What is an IFSC code?</h2></div>
<p style="font-size:13.5px;color:#2A3A50;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:10px">IFSC (Indian Financial System Code) is an 11-character alphanumeric code that uniquely identifies every bank branch in India. The first 4 characters are the bank code, the 5th character is always '0', and the last 6 characters are the branch code.</p>
<p style="font-size:13.5px;color:#2A3A50;line-height:1.8">You need the IFSC code for NEFT, RTGS, IMPS, and UPI transfers. Most online banking apps auto-fill this when you add a beneficiary, but sometimes you need to enter it manually.</p>
